Digital services provider Impax Business Solutions has launched the Microsoft Dynamics Business Central available on cloud in the Kenyan market as it marks its 18th anniversary. Speaking during the launch on Thursday, Microsoft Country Manager Kendi Ntwiga Nderitu lauded the companies efforts in attainment of the milestone. The company says technology has become a more important arm of business as the COVID-19 pandemic ravages economies. “The future is tech and we have seen how this has made the world a global village. The adoption of new technologies to be implemented in multiple sectors of the economy and industries will aid unlock new pathways for innovation, economic growth, service delivery and job creation,” said Ms. Ntwiga. During the celebration of their 18th anniversary that brought together the company’s clients, local and international partners, the Impax CEO Mr. Patrick Mbatia lauded the stakeholders for the handholding over the years. “You have been a steering force that has pushed us to go beyond – as we seek to provide high quality products and solutions for your dire business needs. This is a wake-up call that there is massive potential to tap that will positively impact the economic landscape of our nation and region,” said Mr. Mbatia. Also Read: Impax has over the years grown and expanded their product and services offering to include Microsoft Dynamics 365, Microsoft 365 and Retail Management Systems that span Financials, Supply Chain & Logistics, Human Resources & Talent, Operations Management and Office Productivity. As a Gold Partner of Microsoft in Kenya and awarded the partner of the year in 2017, Impax Business Solutions continues to advance efforts to make the IT industry rich to be an avenue of empowerment and a hub of entrepreneurship. Video Of The Day: | CHASING HOPE | KEMRI undertaking stem cell research for treatment of Leishmaniasis